// @test regression/INV051-method-name-keyword
// @description A method name may be a reserved word, not only a plain identifier. TV accepts `method type(...)`, `method float(...)`, `method label(...)`; we previously rejected these with "Expected method name after 'method'". The `method <name> (` shape (name followed by LPAREN) is what marks a declaration. See investigations/INV051-method-contextual-keyword/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects no-errors
//@version=6
indicator("t")
method type(string str) =>
    str
method float(int id) =>
    id
a = "EMA".type()
b = (7).float()
plot(close)
